      "writtenOn": "2019-08-06T12:55:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right; in my mind there are three \"levels\":\n1. Write out the k8s config files but don\u0027t \"kubectl apply them\".\n2. Write out the k8s config files and apply them.\n3. Write out the k8s config files, apply them, commit and push.\n\nAt the moment, I like doing #1, inspecting the k8s config changes and manually applying and pushing as desired.  It may be that that use case diminishes in the future as we trust the automation more.  One could also make the argument that #2 is not needed, since we don\u0027t care all that much about churn in the config repos, but my current workflow is to only push manually.  Again, that might change as we trust the automation more.",
      "parentUuid": "1eae2718_a1c6f739",
      "revId": "2fa6634f91c4d640da1200cf7f0a1f8ba934e553",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
